article.headline: Lafayette 86, American 83
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Winston Davis reeled off a 3-pointer, an off balance jumper, and another 3-pointer in overtime to lead Lafayette in a come-from-behind 86-83 victory over American on Friday. American had a 26-13 lead early and looked completely in control of the game. But Lafayette gradually got back in the game, drawing to within 7 at the half, and then taking the lead 6 minutes into the second half only to let it slip as American scored 8 unanswered points. But Lafayette fought back again, tying the game 66-66 on a Rob Dill jumper with 7 minutes to play. A costly foul on Jason Thomas on an Andres Rodriguez free-throw miss allowed Lafayette to pull to within two with eleven seconds left as Mike Farrell hit both free throws. Another missed free throw by Rodriguez led to the game-tying dunk by Jernavis Draughn (15 points, 11 rebounds, 3 blocks, 2 assists) with one second left, knotting the score 75-75. Lafayette (15-4, 6-0) scored first in overtime and did not relinquish the lead thanks to strong perimeter play by Davis and Justin DeBerry (15 points, 10 assists, 3 steals). Both teams had five players in double figures led by Raimondas Petrauskas, the game's high scorer with 16, for American (10-10, 4-2) and DeBerry for Lafayette. Lafayette has won its last six games and remains in first in the Patriot League standings.
